  "text": "Tibias were removed between the tibial-tarsal joint and the tibial-femoral joint. Bone strength of both the tibia and femur was analyzed using a TA.XT plus texture analyzer (Stable Microsystems, Guildford, UK) set up with a 50 kg load cell and 3 point-bend fixture [CITATION_1] . Firstly, the bones were defleshed of muscle and tissue by hand using a scalpel. The texture analyzer was set to measure force in compression; test speed was set at 1 mm/sec, and trigger force was set at 7 g (0.069 N). The defleshed bone was placed on the fixtures, a test was run and the peak force in Newtons was recorded. Bone strength per kilogram bird BW was also calculated.",
